WEBVTT

00:07.170 --> 00:09.220
-I am Lieutenant Carlito Blanco.

00:09.230 --> 00:14.090
I am a bad cop and San Toledo is my pueblo.

00:14.100 --> 00:16.060
-(whispering): We've got to get out of here, Lotti.

00:16.070 --> 00:18.000
-Our best chance of seeing Mum and Lotti again

00:18.010 --> 00:20.140
is by doing exactly what Blanco says.

00:20.150 --> 00:22.230
-You're gonna impersonate a Catalan gangster?

00:23.000 --> 00:25.110
-Vic:  The boys are walking   into a trap at the airport.

00:28.130 --> 00:30.080
Nobody shoots at my son.

00:30.090 --> 00:32.140
-Wait, you know where Mum and Lotti are and you didn't tell me?

00:32.150 --> 00:34.060
-Billy:  We tracked 'em   to a stash house   up in the hills.

00:34.070 --> 00:37.040
-We're gonna need a lot more guns.

00:54.090 --> 00:56.040
-(indistinct chatter)

00:56.050 --> 00:57.230
-Lotti: What is this place?

00:58.000 --> 00:59.090
-Lily: Oh, blimey, it's freezing in here.

00:59.100 --> 01:00.130
-Charlie: Some place.

01:00.140 --> 01:02.060
Looks like it's been closed for years.

01:02.070 --> 01:03.200
-(indistinct chatter)

01:03.210 --> 01:06.070
-Billy: Somebody find the whisky?

01:06.080 --> 01:08.210
-Lily: Okay, let's light the fires, put any dry wood in there.

01:08.220 --> 01:10.000
-We'll deal with it.

01:10.010 --> 01:12.030
-Lily: Let's make a fire. Come on, Billy, you were a Boy Scout.

01:12.040 --> 01:13.070
-(grunts)

01:13.080 --> 01:15.080
♪ ♪

01:21.060 --> 01:23.070
-(shivering)

01:28.080 --> 01:30.160
-It's a lot colder than I imagined for the south of Spain.

01:33.020 --> 01:34.190
-We lost everything.

01:37.020 --> 01:38.100
What are we gonna do now?

01:38.110 --> 01:40.200
-Was supposed to be our early retirement, this.

01:42.080 --> 01:44.100
-We'll be back on our feet soon enough.

01:44.110 --> 01:45.200
Hate 'Em and I will see to that.

01:45.210 --> 01:49.030
-Yeah, I'll have a sniff around, see if there's anything of value around here.

01:49.040 --> 01:50.130
Just leave it to me, all right?

01:50.140 --> 01:52.110
-We're not going back to the way things were.

01:52.120 --> 01:54.190
It doesn't work. Look at us.

01:57.080 --> 01:58.200
-Wh-what are you thinking, Al?

01:59.180 --> 02:02.190
-Yeah. We can't just sit on our hands.

02:03.090 --> 02:05.190
-Yeah, son. What you got in mind?

02:06.100 --> 02:08.080
-What can we all put together now?

02:08.090 --> 02:09.230
If we all chucked in?

02:10.110 --> 02:11.230
I mean, watches, jewelry,

02:12.000 --> 02:13.140
everything we brought on the way here.

02:14.080 --> 02:16.000
What we got?

02:17.220 --> 02:19.010
None of ya?

02:21.010 --> 02:22.040
Okay, here.

02:23.230 --> 02:25.120
I'll go first, then, shall I?

02:29.000 --> 02:31.160
That there. Right? That's me.

02:35.040 --> 02:37.040
♪ ♪

02:52.040 --> 02:53.060
-(sighs)

02:54.160 --> 02:56.130
-Come on, Hate 'Em. Cough it up.

03:05.090 --> 03:06.130
What the hell is that?

03:06.140 --> 03:08.050
-It's an antique tooth extractor,

03:08.060 --> 03:10.070
circa Paris, 17th century.

03:10.080 --> 03:11.140
-(laughter)

03:11.150 --> 03:13.090
-Of course. Silly question.

03:17.210 --> 03:19.010
-Albert: Dad?

03:28.010 --> 03:29.100
-Hate 'Em (chuckling): Jeez!

03:30.200 --> 03:31.230
-Rainy-day readies, son.

03:32.000 --> 03:33.110
-Rainy-day readies.

03:35.130 --> 03:36.170
-What do you wanna do, Albert?

03:37.190 --> 03:39.130
-Well, that's simple, innit?

03:41.110 --> 03:43.050
We're going straight.

03:43.060 --> 03:45.060
-(theme music playing)

03:45.070 --> 03:47.070
-(siren wailing)

03:51.190 --> 03:53.180
-Man:  Do we have the stones,   the diamonds?

03:55.040 --> 03:56.120
Where are you taking   the diamonds?

03:58.150 --> 03:59.140
(laughter)

03:59.150 --> 04:01.150
♪ ♪

04:18.130 --> 04:19.140
-Charlie: Hate 'Em.

04:20.020 --> 04:21.170
-Hmm. -Do you...

04:22.010 --> 04:24.000
Do you mind being number two?

04:24.010 --> 04:25.060
-What do you mean?

04:25.210 --> 04:26.220
-Well...

04:27.170 --> 04:29.150
you've always been Vic's right-hand man.

04:29.160 --> 04:32.180
Although, I mean, that's how it seems from the outside.

04:33.150 --> 04:34.160
Do you ever wanna...

04:35.150 --> 04:36.160
I don't know,

04:37.120 --> 04:38.150
lead?

04:41.010 --> 04:42.030
-Look,

04:43.010 --> 04:44.190
being number two's the best gig there is.

04:45.070 --> 04:47.060
You get to have all the fun with no pressure.

04:48.050 --> 04:50.080
You gotta let them believe that all your good ideas

04:50.090 --> 04:51.150
are their good ideas.

04:53.080 --> 04:54.110
Let 'em think that their bollocks

04:54.120 --> 04:56.200
is worth listening to, and you laugh at their jokes.

05:01.010 --> 05:02.180
And you get to watch someone's back,

05:04.050 --> 05:05.130
like a samurai.

05:07.080 --> 05:08.130
It's honorable, son.

05:09.140 --> 05:10.170
-Hmm.

05:11.080 --> 05:12.150
-Honorable.

05:13.020 --> 05:15.040
-(vehicle approaching) -We're on. We're on.

05:21.210 --> 05:23.130
Buenos dias,  Manny.

05:24.030 --> 05:25.100
I see you've got my bits.

05:27.230 --> 05:29.040
-(clicking tongue)

05:29.050 --> 05:30.230
You pay me first this time.

05:31.000 --> 05:32.120
-Do what, mate?

05:32.130 --> 05:34.040
-Dinero.  Mon-ey.

05:34.050 --> 05:37.140
-Listen, I've got something better than money.

05:43.180 --> 05:45.160
-Que? Que cono es esto?

05:46.100 --> 05:47.100
-What'd he say?

05:47.110 --> 05:49.050
-I think he wants to know what they are, Hate 'Em.

05:49.060 --> 05:50.100
-Them?

05:50.110 --> 05:53.010
Cock exploders. Cock exploders, son.

05:53.020 --> 05:56.110
Now, don't take more than one every eight hours,

05:56.120 --> 05:58.050
and keep yourself hydrated at all times.

05:58.060 --> 05:59.170
Come on, Chaz, we're out of here.

05:59.180 --> 06:01.070
-Que cojones!

06:01.080 --> 06:02.080
Oye.

06:02.090 --> 06:03.050
Hey!

06:03.060 --> 06:04.170
♪ Make it boom! ♪

06:04.180 --> 06:06.010
"To... Toromenn"?

06:08.000 --> 06:09.100
♪ Here we go ♪

06:11.050 --> 06:13.130
-We might only be five, but we ain't just any five,

06:13.140 --> 06:14.180
right, boys?

06:15.130 --> 06:16.200
Let's go and get our girls.

06:16.210 --> 06:18.070
-(gun cocks)

06:18.080 --> 06:20.080
♪ ♪

06:35.170 --> 06:36.160
-Do you hear anything?

06:36.170 --> 06:37.210
-Nothing at all.

06:40.030 --> 06:41.190
Lotti, I think we should break out again.

06:42.040 --> 06:43.200
I'm not waiting here like a sitting duck.

06:43.210 --> 06:44.190
-All right, let's go.

06:45.100 --> 06:46.110
-(lock rattles)

06:47.130 --> 06:48.180
-Albert: You sure this is the place?

06:48.190 --> 06:50.000
