06:51.230 --> 06:53.000
-Looks a bit fishy.

06:53.010 --> 06:54.010
I don't see any girls.

06:54.020 --> 06:55.000
-Trust me.

06:55.180 --> 06:57.130
They were all over this place last night.

06:58.030 --> 07:00.200
-You think that Cuban-heel-wearing mug is expecting us?

07:01.050 --> 07:02.220
-There's only one way to find out.

07:08.100 --> 07:10.100
♪ ♪

07:16.070 --> 07:18.230
-♪ I've been a gambling man ♪

07:20.140 --> 07:23.050
♪ I've been a gambling man ♪

07:24.090 --> 07:27.160
♪ They shipped me off   to another land ♪

07:28.140 --> 07:31.090
♪ With a gun in my hand ♪

07:32.080 --> 07:33.080
-(thudding)

07:39.160 --> 07:40.160
-(grunts)

07:44.140 --> 07:45.170
-Anything?

07:46.150 --> 07:47.170
-Nothing.

07:48.170 --> 07:50.180
-Charlie: There's nobody here. -Billy: There's bullet holes.

07:53.040 --> 07:54.110
Something went down here.

07:57.050 --> 07:58.040
-Hate 'Em: Vic...

07:59.090 --> 08:00.090
You need to come see this.

08:14.040 --> 08:15.040
-Vic: They were here.

08:16.170 --> 08:19.060
That son of a bitch locked my Lily in a cage.

08:20.010 --> 08:21.180
-So if they were here, whose blood is that?

08:21.190 --> 08:23.180
-That-that could be anyone's blood.

08:24.090 --> 08:26.050
God knows how many people he's had hostage in here.

08:26.060 --> 08:28.200
-No, not my Lily.

08:50.000 --> 08:51.190
-Lily: I'm not waiting here like a sitting duck.

08:51.200 --> 08:53.010
-All right, let's go.

08:53.120 --> 08:54.190
-(lock rattles)

08:55.100 --> 08:56.100
-Lily: Fuck.

08:57.160 --> 08:59.080
-(speaking Spanish)

08:59.090 --> 09:00.170
-(grunting)

09:00.180 --> 09:02.090
-(both screaming)

09:03.150 --> 09:04.210
-(panting)

09:04.220 --> 09:07.050
-What are you gonna do with that, little girl, huh?

09:09.060 --> 09:10.170
-(grunts) -(screaming)

09:16.130 --> 09:20.180
-♪ Big dreams, baby, yeah,   we have big dreams ♪

09:20.190 --> 09:24.210
♪ A taste for venom   and expensive things ♪

09:24.220 --> 09:25.230
-(woman moaning)

09:26.000 --> 09:29.220
♪ Big dreams, baby, yeah,   we have big dreams ♪

09:30.070 --> 09:34.140
♪ And we're gonna make you   do bad things ♪

09:34.150 --> 09:35.230
-(moaning)

09:35.230 --> 09:37.080
(speaking Spanish)

09:38.080 --> 09:39.140
(speaking Spanish)

09:49.010 --> 09:50.000
-(gasps)

09:50.090 --> 09:51.130
Carlito.

09:54.050 --> 09:55.050
-Run!

09:56.150 --> 09:59.010
-(speaking Spanish)

10:03.020 --> 10:04.050
-(grunts)

10:04.060 --> 10:05.110
-Go! Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

10:07.210 --> 10:08.230
-(man yells)

10:11.220 --> 10:13.010
-(indistinct shouting in Spanish)

10:13.160 --> 10:14.150
-(gunshot)

10:14.160 --> 10:15.190
-Get in the car!

10:18.110 --> 10:19.110
-(gunshot)

10:22.000 --> 10:23.050
-(indistinct shouting in Spanish)

10:25.010 --> 10:26.010
-(engine cranking)

10:26.160 --> 10:27.170
-(groans)

10:29.010 --> 10:30.150
-Right in the fucking balls.

10:33.180 --> 10:35.110
-(groans) -(engine revving)

10:39.120 --> 10:40.100
-Get in!

10:45.170 --> 10:46.130
Vamos! Vamos!

10:49.230 --> 10:51.140
-(indistinct shouting in Spanish)

11:06.230 --> 11:08.210
-So somebody left in a hurry.

11:08.220 --> 11:09.230
-Yeah?

11:10.100 --> 11:11.170
My money's on the girls.

11:11.180 --> 11:13.100
-We're gonna grab Blanco.

11:13.110 --> 11:15.090
I don't give a flying fuck if he's a cop.

11:15.100 --> 11:17.230
-I'll put the fat pig in the brazen bull, Vic,

11:18.000 --> 11:19.100
and light a fucking match.

11:34.170 --> 11:36.010
-Do you see 'em? -No, they've gone.

11:36.020 --> 11:37.070
They've gone.

11:37.080 --> 11:38.140
-Lotti: Shit. -What are you doing?

11:38.150 --> 11:40.030
-The car's pulling. -What?

11:43.000 --> 11:44.040
-What? -We're out of petrol.

11:44.050 --> 11:45.170
-You're joking. Shit. -(car beeping)

11:45.180 --> 11:47.010
-Lotti: They're coming.

11:47.020 --> 11:48.040
-We've gotta go.

11:48.050 --> 11:49.060
Come on.

11:50.190 --> 11:52.060
-Mas rapido!

11:52.170 --> 11:53.190
-Move it. -(tires screeching)

12:09.040 --> 12:10.010
-Por aqui.

12:14.010 --> 12:16.010
♪ ♪

12:41.200 --> 12:43.060
-(cell phone vibrating)

12:49.130 --> 12:51.040
-Woman:  Si?  -(Blanco speaking Spanish)

13:01.060 --> 13:03.130
-Billy:  How the hell   are we gonna find Blanco?

13:04.170 --> 13:06.010
-We go pig hunting.

13:06.140 --> 13:08.110
First cop we find, we give him to Hate 'Em.

13:09.000 --> 13:10.150
He'll tell us where Blanco is.

13:12.110 --> 13:15.230
-♪ I met a girl, evil doll ♪

13:16.110 --> 13:19.020
♪ She told me   all about her soul ♪

13:19.030 --> 13:22.160
♪ She said you can rattle,   you can rattle and roll ♪

13:22.170 --> 13:26.080
♪ But you better watch out   or you could lose it all ♪

13:28.180 --> 13:30.050
-Sorry, love. Bar's closed.

13:31.050 --> 13:32.030
Bar's closed.

13:32.040 --> 13:33.060
-Lieutenant Blanco told me

13:33.070 --> 13:35.070
you boys are always open for business.

13:37.140 --> 13:38.130
-What does he want?

13:38.140 --> 13:41.080
-He has decided to give you another opportunity

13:41.090 --> 13:44.140
to make things right after the fiasco at the airport.

13:44.150 --> 13:46.060
One of you is coming with me.

13:46.070 --> 13:48.010
-I'll go. -No, you won't.

13:51.220 --> 13:53.010
-You.

13:59.210 --> 14:00.190
-Albert: No, okay?

14:00.200 --> 14:02.020
I'm not doing another job for Blanco.

14:02.030 --> 14:03.170
-You have to go, okay?

14:03.180 --> 14:05.110
It's gonna buy us time to track down the girls.

14:05.120 --> 14:07.100
-Look, if you don't show up, we don't know what he'll do.

14:08.080 --> 14:09.200
You gotta do the job, Al.

14:12.010 --> 14:13.060
Could be worse, mate.

14:16.000 --> 14:16.220
-(door opens)

14:20.120 --> 14:22.140
-So, who are you, then?

14:23.030 --> 14:24.040
-I'm the driver.

14:25.080 --> 14:26.050
Buckle up.

14:35.040 --> 14:36.170
-Lily: Run! Move! -(gasps)

14:36.180 --> 14:38.030
-Lily: Go! Go! Go! Go! Go!

14:48.070 --> 14:49.080
-Lupe!

14:53.160 --> 14:54.140
-(panting)

15:00.170 --> 15:02.010
(sighs) -Did we lose them?

15:03.120 --> 15:04.120
-I think so.

15:06.060 --> 15:07.040
-Lupe.

15:12.140 --> 15:14.050
-(panting) -Need a minute?

15:14.060 --> 15:16.120
-I need a drink. -(chuckles) Tell me about it.

15:16.130 --> 15:17.180
-(both chuckle)

15:19.140 --> 15:20.210
-Shit! -(indistinct shouting)

15:42.120 --> 15:43.140
-There you go, Vic.

15:45.080 --> 15:46.160
-Let's go hunting.

15:46.170 --> 15:48.000
-Where's Charlie?

15:48.010 --> 15:49.200
-He's out the back, having a smoke.

15:49.210 --> 15:50.180
-Charlie!

15:53.230 --> 15:55.060
-Who the hell are you?

15:55.070 --> 15:56.220
-We are the Catalans.

16:01.150 --> 16:03.090
-(Ortega speaking Spanish)

16:09.100 --> 16:11.050
(applause)

16:14.080 --> 16:15.060
-Come on.

16:18.090 --> 16:19.230
Wait, isn't that the mayor?

16:20.000 --> 16:21.160
-It looks like him.

16:21.170 --> 16:23.000
-Go, go, go, go, go.

16:23.010 --> 16:24.230
-Lo siento.   -Perdona. Perdona.

16:25.000 --> 16:26.040
-Man:  Por favor.   -Perdona.

16:26.050 --> 16:27.120
-Lo siento.   -Perdona.

16:28.130 --> 16:29.220
-Esta bien, esta bien.  -Man:  Si, senor.

16:30.090 --> 16:32.160
-Mr. Mayor Ortega. -Woman:  Senor...

16:32.170 --> 16:34.090
-Woman:  Senor--   -Por favor, por favor.

16:34.100 --> 16:36.170
-We're tourists and we're in big trouble. Can you help us?

16:36.180 --> 16:38.010
-What kind of trouble,  senoritas?

16:38.020 --> 16:39.050
-Lily and Lotti: Uh...

16:39.210 --> 16:41.010
-Man:  Mierda.

16:44.150 --> 16:46.070
-(hip-hop music playing) -(rapping in Spanish)

16:50.190 --> 16:51.200
-(beeps)

16:53.220 --> 16:56.050
-You don't look like the rest of the guys on Blanco's payroll.

16:56.060 --> 16:58.090
-That's because I'm not on Blanco's payroll.

16:58.100 --> 16:59.170
-Who do you work for, then?

16:59.180 --> 17:00.230
-You ask too many questions.

17:01.000 --> 17:02.200
-What can I say, I don't like to work in the dark.

17:02.210 --> 17:04.020
(grunts) -(tires screeching)

17:05.230 --> 17:07.000
-(both grunt)

17:09.100 --> 17:10.120
-I'm freelance.

17:14.210 --> 17:16.210
-So what is this job for Blanco?

17:16.220 --> 17:18.220
-We just have to run a little obstruction.

17:18.230 --> 17:20.050
Shouldn't be a problem.

17:20.160 --> 17:21.190
-Piece of cake, right?

17:21.200 --> 17:22.210
-What does it mean?

17:22.220 --> 17:24.110
-It's easy. It's easy.

17:24.120 --> 17:25.090
-Easy.

17:26.030 --> 17:27.010
Si.

17:27.100 --> 17:29.010
As  uno, dos, tres.

17:29.170 --> 17:31.080
-(engine revving) -(tires screech)

17:33.080 --> 17:34.150
-Vic, if-if you're alive,

17:34.160 --> 17:36.180
and I hope to God you are, and believe it or not,

17:36.190 --> 17:38.000
Lotti and I are all right.

17:38.010 --> 17:39.170
We escaped and...

17:39.180 --> 17:41.210
right into the hands of the bloody mayor, as a matter of fact,

17:41.220 --> 17:42.210
and, uh...

17:42.220 --> 17:44.010
Vic, I...

17:46.230 --> 17:48.010
(sighs)

17:48.020 --> 17:49.080
Pick up your bloody phone, will you?

17:50.070 --> 17:51.160
-(cell phone vibrating)

17:51.170 --> 17:55.000
-Somebody's very keen to contact you.

17:55.010 --> 17:56.100
-I'm a popular guy.

17:59.030 --> 18:00.120
Our friend here seems very upset.

18:00.130 --> 18:02.150
What exactly did you do to him, Hate 'Em?

18:02.160 --> 18:04.080
-Nothing out of the ordinary, Vic.

18:04.090 --> 18:07.110
-Your friend tried to cook me in the belly of a brazen bull.

18:08.080 --> 18:10.000
-Right. Got it.

18:17.030 --> 18:18.180
-We have to be extremely careful, Lotti.

18:18.190 --> 18:21.160
To state the obvious, it would be a very bad idea

18:21.170 --> 18:23.040
for the mayor to find out who we are.

18:23.050 --> 18:25.010
-Thank you for your patience, ladies.

18:25.020 --> 18:27.140
Were you able to reach your friends?

18:27.160 --> 18:30.150
-Uh, no, there was no answer.

18:31.160 --> 18:32.150
-I see.

18:33.140 --> 18:35.010
Well, I'm sure they will turn up.

18:37.110 --> 18:39.180
In the meantime, would you be willing to tell me

18:39.190 --> 18:41.010
what has happened to you?

18:41.020 --> 18:42.010
-Oh.

18:42.020 --> 18:44.150
-It is clear that you've both been through somewhat of an ordeal.

18:46.000 --> 18:47.170
